<dl id="n12032g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12032g">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12032g"> 32(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> beatilles</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">La petite ville du Mont-Saint-Michel, b&acirc;tie au flanc m&eacute;ridional du rocher et que les anciennes chroniques de l&apos;abbaye d&eacute;signent sous le nom pittoresque de pendula villa, comptait &agrave; peine, au XVIIIe si&egrave;cle, 250 habitants. C&apos;&eacute;taient, pour la plupart, des aubergistes, des marchands de b&eacute;atilles et d&apos;objets de p&egrave;lerinage, des marins et des p&ecirc;cheurs. <br><font color="green">[The little city of Mont-Saint-Michel, that is built on the southern flank of the rock and that the old chronicles of the abbey call by the picturesque name of pendula villa, had, in the eighteenth century no more than 250 inhabitants. They were, for the most part, owners of hotels, sellers of b&eacute;atilles and pilgrimage objects, sailors and fishermen.]</font> <small> &Eacute;tienne Dupont, <a name="LMSM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#LMSM"><cite title="source">Les l&eacute;gendes du Mont-Saint-Michel</cite></a> (1924) 174</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
